observations.recommendation:
We recommend that management:
a).  Maintain a special account in the General Fund for the Bayanihan Grant to Cities and Municipalities. Separate financial statements have to be prepared and presented as part of the General Fund for easy monitoring of the utilization and to ensure the availability of this fund to support COVID prevention programs and projects.
b).  Prepare a monthly report on fund utilization and status of implementation of PPAs using the prescribed format;
c).  Post the accumulated reports on the LGU’s website and in at least three (3) conspicuous public places in the locality at the end of every month;
d). The local chief executive (LCE) of the implementing city/municipality shall send a written notice when said reports have been posted on its website to the DBM, House of Representatives, Senate of the Philippines, House Committee on Appropriations, Senate Committee on Finance, and other offices where submission of reports is required under existing laws, rules and regulation.

Require the Local Finance Committee to review the revenue collection efficiency of the LGU;
Exercise taxing power as authorized under Section 142 to 150 of the Local Government Code of 1991 to earn more revenue to augment the funding source of the operations of the municipality;
Explore other income generating activities that the LGU could pursue to increase its revenue.

The personnel in-charge of the inventory-taking should review the entries presented in the Report of the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and make the necessary corrections  and additional entries like the property number, status of the items and its whereabouts;

Management should follow-up and monitor the reconciliation of the account balances by the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer in order to reflect reliable data in the reports;

The Municipal Accountant make the necessary adjustments in the books based on the result of the actual count and reconciliation activities;

