Explore other income generating activities that the LGU could pursue to increase its revenue.

The Municipal Accountant have to record unserviceable assets to the “Other Assets” account for proper presentation in the financial statements;   

The Municipal Accountant make the necessary adjustments in the books based on the result of the actual count and reconciliation activities;

Require the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to maintain stock/ property cards and ledger cards respectively, to properly account the receipt and disposition of the properties and supplies.

